5:
Thanks, everyone, for all your help
during the Halloween event. Today,
we're having a party for everyone
who helped out with management
and security.
8:
My most sincere thanks to our
initiator, Pur Lilie, and to
Headmistress Nihilyana, for
providing the venue!
14:
Whenever I see you all, I'm reminded
of that phrase from Magia Fest.
17:
I hope we will all continue to have a
future together...
21:
However. Right here, right nowâ€”let's
enjoy the moment together! Happy
Halloween!
34:
Thank you, Stella. Though I suppose
I've gone and done something
unsuited to myself again.
37:
...A lot sure has changed. Though I
get the feeling that you've changed
more than anyone.
40:
What I mean is, you're not a little kid
who needs me to teach her lessons
anymore.
43:
...Were you a kid to begin with? Are
you old enough to drink?
52:
Come to think of it, I can't really
picture you and alcohol together. I
wonder if Alk's old enough to drink
yet? Soon, maybe?
55:
Heh, I can't wait. I hope Marina won't
get mad if I drink with him first.
59:
Lots of people have taught me lots
of things.
62:
Like how to play the role of a
monster. Or why some people are
so eager to steal.
70:
...You said that knowledge is my
friend. That I shouldn't be afraid of
learning new things.
72:
But I didn't even understand that
learning new things could be scary...
76:
...But now you do know. And yet, you
keep learning, questioning yourself,
and moving forward.
79:
Stella. As your friend, I couldn't be
more proud of you.
82:
I've made up my mind, too. I'm
going to do and say exactly what I
need to.
96:
Oh, look. The star of tonight's show.
Sorry, should I get outta here?
100:
No, I came to speak to both of you...
I'm sure you knew that, though.
104:
Good work taking care of those
kidnappers. That was quite a job
you pulled off.
107:
That said, it looks like a lot of folks
want to get more acquainted with
you because of that.
110:
You've got quite the reputation now.
Vice Commander Keira wants to
"mobilize the Guild Knights..."
117:
It's exactly as you say, Captain. The
influence and capabilities of the
Guild Knights are far more
significant than they once were.
119:
I can't go on doing nothing more
than guard duty... nor do I intend to.
122:
Memram informed me of the
individuals trying to take advantage
of us.
125:
Only a few of them so far... But
moving forward, it should be a good
place to start.
129:
...I've said this before, but this would
mean trading guard duty for
espionage.
132:
Once you start down that path,
there's no coming back. You okay
with that?
136:
On the contrary, I'm doing this in
order to restore things to how they
once were.
139:
I don't intend to become a spy. I just
want to make sure that the Guild
Knights never cross "the line."
144:
You're referring to the Guild Knights
making an act of aggression... Or
perhaps, being used for that
purpose.
148:
Indeed. No matter what, we cannot
allow that to happen.
150: We exist to protect, not to fight.
153:
I will establish a "good relationship"
with those people. No matter how
those higher-ups intend to take
advantage of us...
157:
The Guild Knights will always strive
to help those in need.
162:
...Wow, such confidence. That's kinda
worrying in its own way, you know?
166:
As long as my friends have my back,
I know I'm capable of doing this.
168: This... is the path I choose to take.
171:
A way to protect everybody is the
only thing that I'm considering now.
173:
I don't have the mental fortitude
required to think about anything
else.
177:
Sheesh... All of the excuses and
misdirection I prepared are gonna
go to waste.
180:
Yeah, I don't really have anything
else to add. How about you, Finn?
184:
...Just be certain to operate within
the law. This won't be like the time
you operated on your own.
192:
I... I think I've been dreaming the
same dream as you and the
captain.
195:
Ever since the day you first said to
me that you wanted to join the Guild
Knights.
206:
Well then, I'll be off. My friends are
waiting for me!
212:
I don't know. I think she could've
asked for a lot more, don't you?
